      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles flicker low, and even the shadows in this room feel heavier than they did before she left. It feels as though the very air has grown thin, leaving me nothing to breathe but the memory of her betrayal. I look at the night outside and I find myself wishing I could simply dissolve into it... to just stop being, and let the darkness take what is left of me. It seems so much more peaceful than this ache.",
